{
  "message": "fuzz(native-cow): fix snapshot oracle + 21 structured seeds\n\nDrop normalize_snapshot from the replay-vs-oracle comparison: it\nfiltered all-zero blocks only on the device side, so any commit with\nan empty (or all-zero) payload \u2014 which replay legitimately zero-pads\nto block_size \u2014 got dropped from `left` while `expected_snapshot`\nstill recorded it, producing a spurious assertion failure.\nInputs [0,1,1,1,0] and [3,4,1,4,3] each reproduce the panic; the\nexisting `seed_*` corpus already happened to trigger it on cargo\nfuzz's first replay pass. Compare raw snapshots directly \u2014 the\nreplay device only contains explicitly-written blocks, so the\nfilter was unnecessary.\n\nAdd 21 structured seeds covering the harness phase space:\n  * synthetic clean across all 4 block_size choices (64/128/256/512)\n  * multi-write (max 3) and multi-commit (max 4) shapes\n  * full-payload-capacity boundary for bs=64 and bs=128\n  * synth mutation modes: zero-CRC, oversized payload_len, append zero block\n  * replay mutation modes: pad-oversized, truncate, reverse commit list\n  * raw-mode coverage at bs=64 and bs=128 (parser rejects garbage)\n  * zero-payload boundary, max-density 4\u00d73 grid\n\n195K runs / 21s post-fix surface no further crashes.",
